title.accessibilityText: Voir le profil de Robert Greening

primarySubtitle.text: I guarantee to reduce company SaaS/Cloud spend by 20-30% annually

summary.text:
Thanks for sharing this Matt.

Just a glance at the graph speaks volumes - companies that pursued growth at all costs are now facing reduced demand for SaaS solutions, prioritising efficiency and tightening their belts.  

Businesses previously fixated on rapid expansion are now reining in their expenditures, consolidating their technology stacks, and actively seeking ways to minimise waste. As the economic downturn prompts a shift towards more prudent fiscal management, the emphasis is no longer solely on growth, but on sustainable growth. 

What does this mean for SaaS companies? It's time for a narrative recalibration.

In today's landscape, being viewed as a cost-saving necessity is far more compelling than being relegated to the "nice to have" (We'll make you money) category.

As we navigate these challenging times, by showcasing the tangible value of our solutions in terms of cost savings, we can not only weather the storm, but emerge stronger and more resilient than ever before. 💪🏻

P.S - Don't take it personally if you've been affected by tech-layoffs or if you're struggling. Take the opportunity to join a company with a solid Product-Market- Fit and triple digit growth like Vertice and be happy again (we're hiring).

#SustainableGrowth #CostSavings #Adaptability #TechStrategy #EconomicShifts #SaaS #Procurement
